    </figure>

    <h3>Curd (Nandini)</h3>
    <p>
      My mother specifically wanted a 250-gram Nandini packet for the next day's meal. Nandini, the state dairy cooperative, manufactures a 200-gram packet — I photographed the packet itself, with the label reading "Net Quantity: 200g." On Instamart, the smallest Nandini size is 500 grams. The 200-gram packet exists as a physical product, is sold across Bengaluru, and is simply not on Instamart's catalog. This is not a supply chain limitation. It is a merchandising decision.
    </p>

    <figure>
      <img src="/images/item-curd.png" alt="Side by side comparison of Nandini curd on Instamart (smallest is 500g) and a photograph of the physical Nandini 200g packet with the label reading Net Quantity 200g" />
